               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>تحفة العروس ونزهة النفوس</p>
                     <p>A well-known Arabic work on women and marriage entitled Tuhfatu'l-'Arús <lb/> wa-Nushatu'n-Nufús, by Abú 'Abdi'lláh Muhammad at-Tíjání (fl. 710/1310). See <lb/> Brockelmann, vol. II, p. 257, and Ahlwardt's Berlin Arabic Catalogue, vol. v, <lb/> pp. 609-610, No. 6386. The work contains twenty-five chapters (unnumbered), <lb/> some of which are subdivided into several sections, all of which are enumerated on <lb/> ff. 6-7. Begins:</p>
                     <p>بعد</p>
                     <p>، فأن <lb/>
                                الحمد لله الذى سوغنا الفضل جزيلًا، وفضّلنا على كثير من خلقه تفضيلا الخ ... اما <lb/>
                                الله تعالى بلطيف حكمته وما اورى فى ابداع العالم من عجائب قدرته خلق الانسان مجبولا على</p>
                     <p>الافتقار الخ</p>
                     <p>The MS., from the Belshah collection acquired in 1920, comprises 200 ff. of <lb/> 18'3 x 12 c. and 19 ll., is written in a poor modern riq'a, and was completed in <lb/> Jumádà 11, 1306/February, 1889.</p>
                  </summary>
